{"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"applyCollideForce","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"to","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"state","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"inout","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SimulationState","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/Graphs\/documentation\/Graphs\/SimulationState","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Graphs15SimulationStateV"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"radius","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Float","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sf"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"strength","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Float","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sf"},{"text":" = 0.7)","kind":"text"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The simulation state to modify. Velocities are updated in place."}]}],"name":"state"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The collision radius for each node. Nodes within 2× this distance"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are considered overlapping."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"radius"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"How strongly to push overlapping nodes apart. A value of 1.0"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"fully resolves overlaps; smaller values allow some overlap. Defaults to 0.7."}]}],"name":"strength"}],"kind":"parameters"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This force detects when nodes are closer than a specified radius and pushes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"them apart. Unlike the many-body force, it only acts on very close nodes,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"making it suitable for preventing visual overlap.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The collision force helps keep the visualization readable by ensuring nodes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"don’t overlap. It’s particularly useful when nodes have varying sizes or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when the many-body repulsion alone isn’t sufficient to prevent overlap."}]},{"anchor":"Behavior","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Behavior"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When two nodes are within twice the collision radius (i.e., their “circles”"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"overlap), a separating force is applied. The force is proportional to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"overlap amount."}]},{"anchor":"Complexity","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Complexity"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"O(N²) where N is the number of nodes. For better performance with many nodes,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"consider using a spatial data structure (not implemented in this version).","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Example","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Example"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Default collision detection","applyCollideForce(to: &state, radius: 5.0)","","\/\/ Stronger collision response","applyCollideForce(to: &state, radius: 10.0, strength: 1.0)"]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Graphs\/documentation\/Graphs"]]},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Graphs\/documentation\/Graphs\/applyCollideForce(to:radius:strength:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Applies a collision 